  <mdb:resourceLineage>
    <mrl:LI_Lineage>
      <mrl:statement>
        <gco:CharacterString>Etude financée par le programme "plateau continental" du BRGM. Elle a bénéficié des résultats des travaux de recherche effectués dans le cadre des programmes GDR marges, Actions Marges et Plateau continental.</gco:CharacterString>
        <lan:PT_FreeText>
          <lan:textGroup>
            <lan:LocalisedCharacterString locale="#FR">Etude financée par le programme "plateau continental" du BRGM. Elle a bénéficié des résultats des travaux de recherche effectués dans le cadre des programmes GDR marges, Actions Marges et Plateau continental.</lan:LocalisedCharacterString>
          </lan:textGroup>
          <lan:textGroup>
            <lan:LocalisedCharacterString locale="#EN">The 1:250,000 scale geological map of the Corsican continental margins was built with the funding of the BRGM's mapping programme, by the BRGM scientific team between 2010 and 2012 in collaboration with the several INSU-CNRS laboratories, in particular the Université de Bretagne Occidentale (UBO) and the Université de Corte (Corsica). It has benefited from research carried out as part of BRGM's "continental shelf" programme and the GDR-Marges and Actions Marges I and II programmes (TOTAL, IFREMER, BRGM, INSU). The mapping of marine domains is based mainly on the interpretation of geophysical data (seismic reflection profiles, bathymetry, backscatter, ..), and rocks and sediment sampled by dregdes, corers, wells, grabs, ….For this map, seismic data (the digital data were processed by the BRGM) and rock samples were acquired between 1980 and 2000, thanks to several oceanographic campaigns: 7B_1967, BACINO-CORSE, BASTIA_70, BOCCA2000 (10.17600/450050), BOCCA99 (10.17600/99450040), CORSTAGE00 (10.17600/450170), CORSTAGE01 (10.17600/1450180), CORSTAGE97 (10.17600/97450250), CORSTAGE98 (10.17600/98450130), CORSTAGE99 ( 10.17600/99450110), CYLICE (10.17600/97080120), DELTARHO2 (10.17600/82001611), DENISE, FLULIG, GEOCORSE2003 (10.17600/3450130), HR02D, LBAR, LIMA1 (10.17600/1430060), LIMA2 (10.17600/1430070), LISA (10.17600/95000020), MACOLIG (10.17600/96450030), MALIGU, MALIS (10.17600/95000010), MARCO (10.17600/95020040), MESIM (10.17600/91004111; 10.17600/91004112), ODYSSEE, SIBONI.</lan:LocalisedCharacterString>
          </lan:textGroup>
        </lan:PT_FreeText>
      </mrl:statement>
    </mrl:LI_Lineage>
  </mdb:resourceLineage>
